# Supabase — reviews + price-request backend (see src/lib/supabase.ts).
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your project values.
# Until both are set, the testimonials section falls back to seed data and the
# "Add a review" / "Ask the price" forms run in offline/demo mode.
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# Cloudflare Turnstile — PUBLIC site key for the captcha on the review/quote/
# contact forms (safe to expose in the browser bundle). When unset, the forms
# skip the captcha (demo mode). Pairs with the TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY edge secret.
# Local test key that always passes: 1x00000000000000000000AA
VITE_TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY=

# ── Server-side only — NOT Vite env vars ──────────────────────────────────────
# These run inside the Supabase Edge Functions (submit-quote / submit-review) and
# must never reach the browser. Set them with `supabase secrets set`:
#
#   TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY  — Cloudflare Turnstile secret key (pairs with the site
#                           key above). Local test key: 1x0000000000000000000000000000000AA
#   TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN    — from @BotFather (submit-quote sends the notification)
#   TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID      — target chat / group / channel id
#   ALLOWED_ORIGIN        — (optional) lock function CORS to your site origin,
#                           e.g. https://namroller.uz  (defaults to "*")
#
# Example:
#   supabase secrets set TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY=... TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=... \
#     TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID=... ALLOWED_ORIGIN=https://namroller.uz
# SUPABASE_URL, SUPABASE_ANON_KEY and SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY are injected into
# functions automatically (the admin-quotes function uses all three).
#
# ── Admin panel (no new Vite vars) ────────────────────────────────────────────
# The admin panel reuses VITE_SUPABASE_URL / VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY above and
# Supabase Auth. Entry: open the site at #/admin-namroller-8f2a (unlisted hash).
# One-time setup in the Supabase dashboard:
#   1. Run supabase/schema/{admins,capability_videos,storage_capabilities}.sql
#      and re-run the updated quote_requests.sql + reviews.sql.
#   2. Storage → create a PUBLIC bucket "capabilities" (the storage SQL also does
#      this) with a size/MIME limit.
#   3. Authentication → Providers/Settings → turn OFF "Allow new users to sign up"
#      (public signup must be disabled — only manually created admins can log in).
#   4. Authentication → Users → Add user (email + password), then grant admin:
#        insert into public.admins (user_id) values ('<uuid from auth.users>');
#   5. Deploy the function:  supabase functions deploy admin-quotes
#   6. (Optional) enable MFA on the admin user for extra protection.
